<h2>Instructions</h2>

<div>
  **Your Website should have (at least) 3 pages:

  <ol>
    <li>
      A **Home** page, that welcomes the visitor and links to the other pages on
      the website.
    </li>
    <li>
      An **About** page, that shares some basic information about the person.
    </li>
    <li>
      A **Works** page, where you showcase some of the work of the person you
      chose.
    </li>
    <li>
      Bonus: A **Photo Gallery** page, displaying some pictures of the
      person/their work.
    </li>
  </ol>

  You should go through the following steps:

  <ol>
    <li>Run `npm init -y` to create a package.json file.</li>
    <li>Run `npm install express` to install the Express package.</li>
    <li>Create a `views/` directory that will hold your `.html` files.</li>
    <li>
      Create a `public/` directory that will hold other static files, such as
      your CSS stylesheets, scripts and images.
    </li>
    <li>Build your Express app in `app.js`.</li>
    <li>Polish your HTML, stylesheets and scripts. Happy coding! ðŸ’™</li>
  </ol>
</div>